Privacy Policy
Boring Report is committed to protecting the privacy of its users. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how it is used, and how it is protected.
By using Boring Report, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not use Boring Report.
Information We Collect
Boring Report may collect analytics data about your use of the app, such as the number of articles you read and the duration of your sessions. We may also collect links that you submit for summarization purposes, though this is not guaranteed.
How We Use Your Information
The analytics data we collect is used to improve the app and your overall experience. We may also use it to identify and fix bugs or other issues.
Data Protection
Boring Report does not collect any personally identifiable information. All data is collected and stored in a secure manner, and we take appropriate measures to protect it from unauthorized access or disclosure.
Changes to this Policy
Boring Report reserves the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes via the app or other means, and your continued use of the app after such notification constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at v@boringreport.org.